    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Stan Arts</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://www.computerschaak.nl/index.php/nieuws/51-toernooien/704-pt48-round-7\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/be/TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg/300px-TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"198\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/be/TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg/450px-TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/be/TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg/600px-TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:TheBaronNementonPT48.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a> and <a href=\"/Richard_Pijl\" title=\"Richard Pijl\">Richard Pijl</a> @ <a href=\"/PT_48\" title=\"PT 48\">PT 48</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Stan Arts</b>,<br />\na Dutch computer game and chess programmer, who already started programming with age eight on a <a href=\"/Commodore_64\" title=\"Commodore 64\">Commodore 64</a>, writing programs and games in <a href=\"/Basic\" title=\"Basic\">Basic</a> and <a href=\"/6502\" title=\"6502\">6502</a> <a href=\"/Assembly\" title=\"Assembly\">assembly</a> language, since 1994 on an <a href=\"/X86\" title=\"X86\">486</a> <a href=\"/IBM_PC\" title=\"IBM PC\">PC</a> in <a href=\"/Pascal#TurboPascal\" title=\"Pascal\">Turbo Pascal</a> and inline assembly with focus on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_computer_graphics\">3D graphics</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Chess_Programming\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Programming</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2002_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2002 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Programming\">Chess Programming</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Programming\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In 2002, Stan Arts became interested in chess programming, starting with an <a href=\"/8x8_Board\" title=\"8x8 Board\">8x8 Board</a> and re-inventing <a href=\"/Minimax\" title=\"Minimax\">Minimax</a>. Stan discovered chess programming in the Internet, learned about <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">alpha-beta</a> and met <a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Lauro_Strapasson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"José Lauro Strapasson (page does not exist)\">José Lauro Strapasson</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, author of <a href=\"/index.php?title=PreChess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"PreChess (page does not exist)\">PreChess</a>, who pointed him the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_Pascal\">Free-Pascal</a> compiler and taught him the <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a> protocol <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \nAlready in summer 2002 Stan was able to publish his first WinBoard compatible chess engine dubbed <a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan%27s_Chess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Stan&#39;s Chess (page does not exist)\">Stan's Chess</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, soon also with an own <a href=\"/3D_Graphics_Board\" title=\"3D Graphics Board\">3D Graphics Board</a> <a href=\"/GUI\" title=\"GUI\">GUI</a>, later evolving to <a href=\"/Neurosis\" title=\"Neurosis\">Neurosis</a>. \nHis recent program <a href=\"/Nemeton\" title=\"Nemeton\">Nemeton</a>, also written in Pascal, had its debut at the <a href=\"/PT_47\" title=\"PT 47\">PT 47</a> in 2014, and was released soon after <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>.  \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2002_...\">2002 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2002 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=245041\">Stan´s Chess 1.1</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 10, 2002</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=393228\">Neurosis's Dutch open, and new release</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 25, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/DOCCC_2004\" title=\"DOCCC 2004\">DOCCC 2004</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=433604\">Neurosis 1.9.</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 26, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=137519&amp;t=15688\">Re: movei hash report</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 13, 2007&#160;» <a href=\"/Internal_Iterative_Deepening\" title=\"Internal Iterative Deepening\">Internal Iterative Deepening</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=171349&amp;t=19214\">Re: implementation of undoMove()?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 28, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Unmake_Move\" title=\"Unmake Move\">Unmake Move</a>, <a href=\"/Copy-Make\" title=\"Copy-Make\">Copy-Make</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26580\">Neurosis 2.5 , Programmer's Tournament version</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 16, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=54375\">Nemeton 1 release</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 18, 2014</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=54404\">Legacy hardware emulator chess championship?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 20, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/Commodore_64\" title=\"Commodore 64\">Commodore 64</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=60264\">Hashtable and 50 move rule draws</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 24, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a>, <a href=\"/Fifty-move_Rule\" title=\"Fifty-move Rule\">Fifty-move Rule</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=64177\">Nemeton3D 1.51</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 04, 2017</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=65151\">3D printing chess pieces. Specifically those of Nemeton3D</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 12, 2017 </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=67881\">Nemeton 1.7</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 02, 2018 </li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/stan.arts\">Stan Arts | Facebook</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stan_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/PT_48\" title=\"PT 48\">PT 48</a>, Round 7: <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a> and <a href=\"/Richard_Pijl\" title=\"Richard Pijl\">Richard Pijl</a> in <a href=\"/The_Baron\" title=\"The Baron\">The Baron</a> vs. <a href=\"/Nemeton\" title=\"Nemeton\">Nemeton</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerschaak.nl/index.php/nieuws/51-toernooien/704-pt48-round-7\">PT48 Round 7</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=232745\">Chess Program in Ada 95. (for Pascal or Ada programmers)</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Lauro_Strapasson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"José Lauro Strapasson (page does not exist)\">José Lauro Strapasson</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 29, 2002</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Stanschess.html Stan´s Chess (no longer available) from <a href=\"/WBEC\" title=\"WBEC\">WBEC Ridderkerk</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=245041\">Stan´s Chess 1.1</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 10, 2002</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=54375\">Nemeton 1 release</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stan Arts</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 18, 2014</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301043135\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.017 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.020 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 97/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 206/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:5609-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301043135 and revision id 12279\n -->\n"
